title: Source: Titans to start QB Rudolph against Bills
description: The Titans will start backup QB Mason Rudolph in place of Will Levis against the Bills on Sunday, a source told ESPN, confirming a report by Paul Kuharsky.
author: Turron Davenport

title: Sources: Teams eyeing trade for Jets WR Wilson
description: Teams have inquired into whether the Jets would be willing to trade receiver Garrett Wilson, sources told ESPN.
author: Adam Schefter

title: Cyclist Sir Chris Hoy announces his cancer is terminal
description: The 48-year-old Scot says doctors have told him he has between two and four years to live.

title: Do Arsenal have a red card problem - and could it cost them the title?
description: Just eight games into the Premier League season and Arsenal have already had three players sent off - but just how costly could it be?

title: College football live updates: Georgia-Texas and more
description: No. 5 Georgia is gunning to hand No. 1 Texas its first loss in a must-watch SEC showdown. Follow all the games with us.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Arch Manning takes over for Quinn Ewers in second quarter of No. 1 Texas' game vs. No. 5 Georgia
description: Texas had 15 yards and two turnovers on five possessions with Ewers.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Verstappen wins US GP Sprint as Norris third after last-lap drama
description: World championship leader Max Verstappen ended his lengthy victory drought to win a thrilling United States Grand Prix Sprint as title rival Lando Norris finished third.

title: Verstappen strikes back with US GP Sprint pole as Norris bemoans 'shocking' lap
description: Max Verstappen will start from the head of a Formula 1 grid for the first time in almost four months on Saturday after he took pole position for the Sprint at the United States Grand Prix, with title rival Lando Norris only fourth.
